1. No match ==> <Route path="*"> </Route>

2. use useHistory to go Back from page to page (change the browser history)
    - history.replace() -> redirect
    - history.push -> go

3. promt: this component will automatically watch if we navigate away.

4. useLocation : gives access to a location object which has information about currently loaded page.
    returns the location object that represents the current URL.

5. useRouteMatch:
    Returns a match object that contains all the information like how the current URL matched with the Route path.